---
Midgaard's Roc Road presence is material, ritual, and narrative simultaneously.
Material: the eastern approaches carry ash-mortar paving from the Ash-and-Iron Decades rebuild, characteristic gray-purple volcanic aggregate mortar from Cinderteeth-adjacent quarries.
Ritual: the Three Civic Oaths are recited at every shift change; roadwardens repaint boundary sigils even when manpower prevents full repairs, because the Oath of Stone requires visible evidence of maintained jurisdiction.
The Seven Watches pattern fades by the Crossroads — Lantern Watch increases patrol density through the Banner Hills, but Midgaard's watch cadence is a memory rather than a schedule by mid-band.
Narrative: Midgaard texts portray Roc Road as a civilizing spine extending order westward, a framing the Reckoning faction disputes by pointing to the Unindexed Years and the sealed-warrant corridor evidence.
