Roc Road is Rakuen's most important external connection — the mechanism by which goods, people, and civic communications move between Rakuen and the wider trade network.
Rakuen's dispatch houses track Roc Road conditions continuously.
The road's western anchor (Kiess) and eastern anchor (Midgaard) both affect Rakuen supply chains: Midgaard disruptions affect goods flowing south through the Eccentric Woodland corridor; Kiess disruptions affect goods flowing through the continental trade network.
During Evermeet Collapse-era road militarization, Rakuen's supply dependencies made the city vulnerable to requisitioning that redirected cargo toward Midgaard's emergency provisioning priorities.
Rakuen's institutional memory of that period is the basis for its persistent push to maintain redundant supply lines rather than dependence on the Roc Road alone.

