Mafdet's interest in Roc Road is as the far western end of the continental trade chain that connects eastward through Midgaard's eastern desert routes to Mafdet's harbor.
Goods originating in Kiess's market sphere travel east along Roc Road, through Midgaard, and then via various desert and coastal routes to Mafdet.
Route disruptions on Roc Road appear in Mafdet's cargo scheduling records as "western origin delay" — cargo stuck in Kiess's convoy compact system or delayed at a Roc Road checkpoint.
Mafdet attests origin for goods that pass through its harbor; Roc Road provenance is traceable through the dual-mark manifest system, making western continental goods identifiable in Mafdet's ledgers.

