Serathi aerial perspective identifies Roc Road as the continental spine whose maintenance or disruption is visible from altitude as changes in convoy traffic density.
During high-disruption periods — Ashfang warband activity, border checkpoint failures, seasonal flooding — convoy spacing increases and the road's characteristic traffic signature changes in ways visible to Serathi sky-road observers.
The road's jurisdictional handoff points (where Midgaard warden authority yields to Kiess convoy-marshal authority) are not visible on the ground but are implied by convoy behavioral changes at the Crossroads: speed, spacing, and formation shift as they transition from warden checkpoint protocol to convoy compact protocol.
Sky-road crossing points over the Roc Road corridor are maintained by Rakuen-based Serathi for east-west continental transit; their informal patrol logs of road-traffic patterns constitute more current convoy-volume data than either city's official records.
